; klboards horizon-profile — cross-repo wire contract (RFC 8610 CDDL).
; ADR core-domain/0004 (terrain skyline) · /0006 (provisioning<->runtime invariant) · /0011 · /0018.
;
; A per-site terrain skyline: binding metadata + a packed azimuth->angle array. Integer-keyed CBOR
; map, CDE / core-deterministic, fixed-point integers (float-free). Independently versioned and
; signed (COSE_Sign1; verification deferred) from the parameter vector. The WRITER is
; provisioning-builder (DEM ray-trace); the engine is the reader.

horizon-profile = {
  0 => int,            ; lat_microdeg   -- bound latitude,  microdegrees (north +)
  1 => int,            ; lon_microdeg   -- bound longitude, microdegrees (east +)
  2 => int,            ; elev_mm        -- bound elevation, millimetres
  3 => uint,           ; dem_source     -- registered DEM-source id (e.g. Copernicus GLO-30, USGS 3DEP)
  4 => uint,           ; dem_version    -- DEM dataset version
  5 => 0..2,           ; prov_refraction_model -- model used at provisioning (must match runtime; 0006)
  ? 6 => int,          ; prov_refraction_coeff_micro -- micro-arcminutes (iff prov model = 2)
  7 => angle-array,
}

; The runtime MUST verify (lat,lon,elev) match the site it computes for (the 0004/0006 binding
; invariant) before composing this skyline; a mismatch is the wrong profile -> reject.

; Packed azimuth->horizon-angle samples: a CBOR byte string of little-endian int32 MILLIARCMINUTES
; (1 mam = 1/60000 degree), length a multiple of 4 and >= 4. n = len/4 samples are evenly spaced over
; [0 deg, 360 deg); sample i is the SIGNED skyline altitude at azimuth i*360/n (compass, from North).
; Positive = a ridge above the astronomical horizon (delays sunrise); negative = a depressed sea
; horizon (the Visible-mode dip is just a negative angle). The runtime interpolates linearly with
; 360 deg wraparound and crosses the Sun's upper limb: centre-altitude target = angle - semidiameter.
angle-array = bstr
